g.text: Naive approach : Pick 4 values in O(N^4) time
- Store all pair sums (i1, i2) in map (total pairs: O(N^2)
- For each pair, search for another pair with (target - sum_pair)
One issue with the approach : Indices might repeat.
To counter this, don't precompute all pair sums first,
- We iterate over idx3 and idx4, and search for (idx1, idx2) pairs.
- As we complete the search over a particular idx3, we add the combos
